LOGISTIC REGRESSION

Nguyen Hai Truong

March 1, 2017

Mc tiu nghin cu:

Nghin cu khung l thuyt m hnh hi quy Logistic v cch thc hnh m hnh vi b s liu c sn trong R.

1 Hi quy Logistic

1.1 Khi nim c bn

Trc ht, ta cn nh ngha mt s khi nim c bn sau.

  • Bin nh tnh (qualitative variable): l bin cho bit c hay khng c mt thuc tnh no . Bin nh tnh c th c 2 phm tr (trng thi) hoc nhiu hn th. V d: bin gii tnh (nam, n); bin cht lng sn phm (chnh phm, ph phm); bin vng-min (Bc, Trung, Nam); bin trnh hc vn (Tt nghip cp 3, i hc, Thc s, Tin s) v.v.

  • Bin gi (dummy variable): bin ch nhn hai gi tr 0-1, dng biu din bin nh tnh.

Gi s bin nh tnh Z no c 2 phm tr, s dng bin s nhn gi tr 1 ng vi cc quan st thuc mt trong hai phm tr v nhn gi tr 0 cho phm tr cn li. Bin s nhn gi tr 0-1 ny gi l bin gi tng ng vi bin nh tnh Z. Chng ta c th chn hai gi tr khc bit bt k gn cho hai nhm khc nhau ca bin nh tnh m khng lm thay i bn cht v kt lun ca vn nghin cu.

1.2 Binary Logistic Regression

(gi tt l hi quy Logistic)

L m hnh hi quy khi bin ph thuc l bin nh tnh ch gm 2 trng thi, ta s dng bin gi biu din bin ph thuc. Nh vy, bin ph thuc ch nhn hai gi tr 0 v 1.

M hnh hi quy ny gip ta c th d bo c xc sut khi bin ph thuc nhn gi tr 1 (xc sut bin c xy ra) da vo thng tin cc bin c lp trong m hnh, sau phn loi trng thi ca bin ph thuc.

Xc sut: k hiu l P.

t:

p = P(Y=1/Xj) - xc sut khi bin ph thuc Y nhn gi tr 1 (xc sut bin c xy ra); j=1,,n

(1-p) = 1-P(Y=1/Xj) = P(Y=0/Xj) - xc sut khi Y=0 (xc sut bin c khng xy ra)

Lm th no m hnh ha c mi quan h gia xc sut khi Y nhn gi tr 1 (p) v cc bin c lp (Xj)?

Gi s ta s dng m hnh hi quy tuyn tnh thng thng (linear regression): \[p = B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n\] Ta nhn thy vic chy m hnh s c th gp phi vn : Vi Xj nhn gi tr nh gn ti 0, p c th < 0; cn vi Xj nhn gi tr ln, p c th > 1. Nh vy nhng c lng trn s khng chnh xc v p l xc sut nn ch nhn gi tr t 0 n 1. Hi quy tuyn tnh s khng cn thch hp trong trng hp ny na.

gii quyt vn trn, trong hi quy Logistic ngi ta s dng hm Logistic trong ton hc (logistic function):

\[p_=\frac{exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n)}{1+exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n)}\]

=> \[1-p=\frac{1}{1+exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n)}\]

=> \[\frac{p}{1-p}=exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n)\]

T s trn c gi l Odds (kh nng, t l u th) - cho bit xc sut khi Y=1 (xc sut bin c xy ra) bng bao nhiu ln so vi xc sut khi Y=0 (xc sut bin c khng xy ra). V d, t l h ngho ca mt a phng l 0.25, khi t l h khng thuc h ngho s l 0.75 => Odds = 1/3 - xc sut h ngho bng 1/3 so vi xc sut h khng thuc din h ngho.

=> \[Ln(Odds)=Ln(\frac{p}{1-p}) = B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n\]

Phng trnh trn gi l phng trnh hi quy Logistic. y l mt dng hm Logit, Ln(Odds) l hm hi quy tuyn tnh vi cc bin c lp Xj (Ln: logarit c s e, e~2.71).

c lng cc tham s Bj, ngi ta dng phng php hp l ti a (maximum likelihood), ngha l tm Bj ti a ha hm hp l.

Hm hp l c dng:

Nh vy, bi ton y l: Tm Bj L -> max <=> Tm Bj ln(L) -> max

Khi c lng c cc tham s Bj, vi mi tp gi tr Xj c th ta c th d dng tnh c gi tr c lng ca pi (theo cng thc cp trn). T ta c th phn loi c trng thi ca bin ph thuc da vo vic so snh gi tr c lng pi v ngng gi tr ta chn phn loi.

Ngoi ra, khi ta c gi tr c lng ca Bj v pi, c th xc nh c nu Xj tng 1 n v th xc sut pi s thay i nh th no, hay ni cch khc nh hng ca Xj n pi c th hin qua cng thc sau:

\[\frac{p_i}{X_j} = p_i(1-p_i)B_j\]

xc sut p l 50% th cc bin c (Xj) c mi lin h nh th no?

\[p=\frac{exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n)}{1+exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n)} = \frac{1}{2}\] <=> \[exp(B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n) = 1\]

<=> \[B_0 + B_1X_1 + ... + B_nX_n = 0\]

Phng trnh trn th hin mi lin h gia cc bin c lp Xj khi p = 50%.

1.3 nh gi cht lng m hnh

Confusion matrix dng xc nh xem bao nhiu quan st c phn loi ng v bao nhiu quan st phn loi sai, hay ni cch khc confusion matrix so snh trng thi c d bo vi trng thi thc t ca bin ph thuc.

Dng confusion matrix c th tnh c accuracy ( chnh xc ca m hnh) - t l tng s quan st c d bo ng trn tng quan st. Ngoi ra, cn c th tnh c:

  • True positive rate (TPR), sensitivity: % bin c Y=1 trong thc t c d bo ng

  • False negative rate (FNR): % bin c Y=1 trong thc t d bo sai

  • True negative rate (TNR), specificity: % bin c Y=0 trong thc t c d bo ng

  • False positive rate (FPR), 1-specificity: % bin c Y=0 trong thc t d bo sai (thc t l Y=0 nhng d bo l Y=1)

  • Precison = PPV (positive predicted value): trong s quan st c d bo l Y=1 c bao nhiu % quan st c d bo ng

ROC (Receiver Operating Characteristic) curve khi qut cht lng m hnh bng vic biu th mi quan h gia true positive rate (sensitivity) v false positive rate (1-specificity) tng ng vi mi ngng phn loi khc nhau.

Ta din gii chi tit cch v ng ROC nh sau: Gi s ta mun xem 1 KH c kh nng tr n hay khng, bin ph thuc l KH c 2 trng thi l v n(=1) v khng v n (=0). S dng hi quy Logistic ta d bo c xc sut v n ca KH, sau ta chn gi tr ngng phn loi trng thi KH (V d: pi > 0.5 - KH v n; pi <= 0.5 - KH khng v n => nh vy ngng y ta chn l 0.5). ng vi mi gi tr ngng khc nhau s l 1 im c ta (false positive rate, true positive rate). Tp hp cc im ny (tc vi nhng s la chn ngng khc nhau) s to thnh ng ROC.

ng ROC nm cng hng v pha nh gc bn tri th chnh xc ca d bo cng cao, iu th hin true positive rate cao v false positive rate thp; cn nu cng tin ti ng cho 45 so vi trc honh th chnh xc ca d bo cng km. ng cho 45 so vi trc honh th hin s phn loi l khng c ngha (do true positive rate = false positive rate).

AUC (Area under ROC curve) - din tch pha di ng cong ROC, l thc o chnh xc ca s phn loi. AUC cng ln th chnh xc cng cao.

  • AUC t 0.5-0.6: Fail

  • 0.6-0.7: Poor

  • 0.7-0.8: Fair

  • 0.8-0.9: Good

  • trn 0.9: Excellent

#create a dummy variable
contrasts(Direction)

Ta t bin gi biu din bin ph thuc - xu hng hin ti ca th trng (Direction). Direction nhn 2 gi tr:

  • Direction = 1 - th trng i ln

  • Direction = 0 - th trng i xung

pi = P(Direction=1/Lag1,,Lag5,Volume) - xc sut th trng c xu hng i ln

(1-pi) = P(Direction=0/Lag1,,Lag5,Volume) - xc sut th trng c xu hng i xung

Pseudo R squared L h s (nhn gi tr t 0 n 1) cho bit mc gii thch s thay i ca bin ph thuc bi cc bin c lp trong m hnh hi quy Logistic, tng t nh R squared trong OLS. Pseudo R squared cng cao th mc gii thch s thay i ca bin ph thuc bi cc bin c lp trong m hnh cng cao.

\[pseudo.R^2 = 1-\frac{residual.deviance}{null.deviance}\]

Pseudo R squared trong m hnh ny ~ 0 chng t cc bin c lp gn nh khng gii thch c g s thay i ca bin ph thuc (Direction).

#classification: up/down

Ta d bo xc sut th trng i ln trong ngy hin ti, sau ta s chn ngng 0.5 phn loi:

  • Nhm c xc sut > 0.5 - th trng c xu hng i ln (Up)

  • Nhm cn li - th trng c xu hng i xung (Down)

Ta thy s ngy th trng i xung c d bo ng l 145 ngy, s ngy th trng i ln c d bo ng l 507 ngy. Vy tng s ngy d bo ng xu hng th trng l: 145+507=652 ngy.

#% correct classification

ROC curves

# ROC curves on training test and testing set
pred_train <- predict(glm.fit3, Smarket.before2005, type = "response") 

pred_test <- predict(glm.fit3, Smarket.2005, type = "response") 

ROCpred_train <- prediction(pred_train, Smarket.before2005$Direction) #transform the input data into a standardized format

ROCpred_test <- prediction(pred_test, Smarket.2005$Direction)

ROCperf_train <- performance(ROCpred_train, "tpr", "fpr")

ROCperf_test <- performance(ROCpred_test, "tpr", "fpr")

plot(ROCperf_train)

plot(ROCperf_test, col = "red", add =T)

AUC

auc_train <- performance(ROCpred_train, "auc", "cutoff")

# GAIN charts on training test and testing set

plot(GAINperf_test, col = "red", add =T)

3 Nhng thng tin thm

3.1 Bin c lp l bin nh tnh

Trong trng hp bin c lp l bin nh tnh c 2 phm tr, c th s dng 1 bin gi 0-1 biu din thng tin nh tnh ny. Khi bin c lp l bin nh tnh c m phm tr (m>2), cn (m-1) bin gi 0-1.

V d, bin loi hnh doanh nghip c 3 phm tr: nh nc, t nhn, FDI. C th s dng 2 bin gi sau:

  • NN: NN=1 - doanh nghip nh nc, NN=0 - khng phi doanh nghip nh nc

  • TN: TN=1 - doanh nghip t nhn, TN=0 - khng phi doanh nghip t nhn

Nh vy, cc doanh nghip nh nc s ng vi (NN=1, TN=0), doanh nghip t nhn (NN=0, TN=1), doanh nghip FDI (NN=0, TN=0). Nhm doanh nghip FDI c gi l phm tr c s - phm tr ng vi trng hp tt c cc bin gi nhn gi tr 0.

3.2 WoE & IV

3.2.1 Khi nim

WoE (Weight of Evidence) miu t mi quan h gia bin c lp v bin ph thuc theo categories (phm tr) ca bin ph thuc. Cn IV (Infomation Value) o lng mnh ca mi quan h .

Din gii mt cch chi tit, gi s bin ph thuc - KH c 2 categories (phm tr): Good (KH=1) & Bad (KH=0). Bin c lp - Tui nhn cc gi tr khc nhau: 16,20,21,32 WoE s gip ta chia bin Tui thnh cc nhm (bins/groups) (v d: <22; 22-25; 25-30; 30-40; 40-50; >50). ng vi mi nhm tui s c s lng KH good/bad nht nh v gi tr WoE tng ng.

Cng thc tnh WoE: \[WoE=ln(\frac{Distr. Goods}{Distr. Bads})\] Trong : \[Distr.Goods = \frac{Goods}{Total - of - Goods}\] \[Distr.Bads = \frac{Bads}{Total - of - Bads}\] S c 3 trng hp:

  • WoE = 0 khi Distr.Goods = Distr.Bads

  • WoE < 0 khi Distr.Goods < Distr.Bads

  • WoE > 0 khi Distr.Goods > Distr.Bads

Cng thc tnh IV: \[IV=\sum[(Distr.Goods_i - Distr.Bads_i)*WoE_i] ; i=1,..,n\]

  • IV < 0.02: bin c lp khng c ngha trong m hnh ( phn chia Good/Bad bin ph thuc)

  • 0.02 - 0.1: bin c lp c mi lin h yu vi bin ph thuc - weak relationship

  • 0.1 - 0.3: medium relationship

  • trn 0.3: strong relationship

3.2.2 V d

Ta xem v d sau:

nhm tui 21-24: c 82 Goods (KH tt), 52 Bads (KH xu). Tng s KH tt ca tt c cc nhm tui l 700, KH xu - 300.

=> Distr.Goods = 82/700 ~ 0.11714; Distr.Bads = 52/300 ~ 0.17333

WoE = ln(0.11714/0.17333) ~ -0.3918;

Cumulative IV tng ng vi nhm tui trn = (0.11714-0.17333)*(-0.3918) = 0.0220.

=> IV = tng Cumulative IV ca tng nhm tui = 0.089 - bin c lp (Tui) c mi lin h yu vi bin ph thuc.

3.2.3 Thc hnh trong R

Trong R c kh nhiu package dng tnh WoE v IV nh: Information, woe, riv, smbinning v.v.

y ta s s dng mt trong s thc hnh - smbinning package

IV ca TOB y bng 0.5025 - chng t bin c lp TOB c mi lin h mnh vi bin ph thuc (FlagGB). Ngoi ra, nhn vo $ivtable ta thy bin TOB c chia thnh 5 nhm (5 Cutpoint). Trong cc nhm c nhm khuyt d liu (Missing), v ta mun gp nhm vo nhm m c gi tr WoE gn nht vi gi tr WoE ca nhm Missing.

attach(result)
attach(ivtable)
a <- 1:length(Cutpoint)        #a- stt ca Cutpoint
b <- a[Cutpoint == "Missing"]  #b- stt ca Missing Cutpoint

d = c()
for (i in 1:(b-1))           #i- stt ca WoE 
 {
 d[i] = abs(WoE[i] - WoE[Cutpoint == "Missing"])   #d- chnh lch gia WoE ca nhm Missing v cc nhm khc 
 }

index_d <- 1:length(d)       #index_d- stt ca d

d <- as.data.frame(d)
d$index_d <- index_d

e <- index_d[d$d == min(d$d)]  #e- stt ca min(d)

#chuyn Cutpoint mang gi tr Missing thnh <=63 (WoE ca Cutpoint Missing gn nht vi WoE ca Cutpoint <=63)
ivtable$Cutpoint[ivtable$Cutpoint == "Missing"] <- ivtable$Cutpoint[e]

Lu

Khi s dng smbinning package, ta cn phi thu thp v x l s liu sao cho:

  • Bin ph thuc ch nhn 2 gi tr 0-1, nh dng cn phi l integer (int)

  • Bin c lp cn phi c t nht 10 gi tr khc nhau, nh dng cn phi l numeric hoc factor.
